main event: A private pilot reported seeing lights moving east to west at a high rate of speed on 16 October 1966.
interesting points: The lights were observed south of Greenville, Ohio at approximately 7:00 p.m.,The observation was relayed through the FAA, indicating a level of corroboration,The Air Force was notified and responded to the report,The document signifies a request for more information from the observer,The conclusion noted insufficient data for evaluation.
